========,1,preface.
Bucks Lake (also, Bucks Lodge) is a census-designated place (CDP) in Plumas County, California, United States.
Bucks Lake is located on the south shore of the lake of the same name, west-southwest of Quincy.
The population was 10 at the 2010 census, down from 17 at the 2000 census.
========,2,History.
The area was first established as a ranch by Horace Bucklin and Francis Walker in 1850.
A hotel and a post office were later built on the site.
In 1928, Bucks Storage Dam was built on Bucks Creek, a tributary of the Feather River, creating the Bucks Lake reservoir, inundating the original site of the town.
The Bucks Lake post office operated from 1940 to 1942.
Bucks Lake is now registered as California Historical Landmark #197.
